      "id": "t58",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Do YouTube Shorts count toward the YPP threshold?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t59",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Yes — 10 million Shorts views in 90 days qualifies you for the YouTube Partner Program, equivalent to the 4,000 watch hours requirement for long-form content."
    },
    {
      "id": "t60",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Why do Shorts pay so much less than regular videos?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t61",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Ads appear between Shorts in the feed rather than on individual videos, creating a shared, indirect revenue pool that dilutes per-creator earnings significantly."
    },
    {
      "id": "t62",
      "tag": "button",
      "text": "Should I focus on Shorts or long-form for income?"
    },
    {
      "id": "t63",
      "tag": "div",
      "text": "Use Shorts for audience growth, long-form for income. A viral Short that adds 50,000 subscribers can multiply your long-form earnings far more than the Short itself earns."
